  "text": "Previous data have shown that EGFR expression is high in Pax6-and nestin-positive precursor cells in the subventricular zone, and that expression is asymmetric in dividing precursor cells leaving the ventricular zone and SVZ when they start to migrate as early neurons to the cortical plate [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Consistent with these results, we found a high degree of TrkB and EGFR coexpression in neural cells in E13 forebrain (Fig. 2d) .",
